# MFW-PyQt6 AI Rules

- Treat `.github/copilot-instructions.md` as the canonical project architecture guide.
- `app/core/service/` and `app/core/runner/` must not add new direct imports of `app.common.signal_bus.signalBus`.
- Prefer `Runner Signal -> ServiceCoordinator -> signalBus -> View` for runtime notifications.
- View code should call `ServiceCoordinator` methods instead of mutating model state or reaching into service internals.
- Widget code must stay UI-only and must not import Core, Service, or `ServiceCoordinator`.
- Keep business logic out of View; keep UI logic out of Core/Service.
- Use snake_case for modules, functions, methods, variables, attributes, and signals.
- Use PascalCase for classes and exceptions; use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants.
- Use `self.tr("...")` for user-visible text in View and Runner code.
- Avoid blocking the UI thread; prefer `@asyncify`, async flows, and `QTimer.singleShot` for delayed UI actions.
